 t each performance.<br /><br />The <em>New York Times</em> Critic&rsquo\;s
  Pick returns.<br /><br />After a hit run at Audible&rsquo\;s Minetta Lane
  Theatre\, <em>Mexodus</em>&nbsp\;comes back to Off-Broadway for a strictl
 y limited engagement.<br /><br />Hailed by <em>The New York Times</em> as 
 &ldquo\;an electrifying theatrical experience&rdquo\; and named &ldquo\;th
 e season&rsquo\;s first must-see musical&rdquo\; by <em>The Wrap</em>\, <e
 m>Mexodus</em> is a thrilling\, genre-defying hip-hop musical created and 
 performed by Brian Quijada and Nygel D. Robinson\, and directed by David M
 endiz&aacute\;bal.<br /><br />Told through live looping\, bold storytellin
 g\, and sick beats\, <em>Mexodus</em> reimagines the Underground Railroad 
 heading south to Mexico&mdash\;unearthing a powerful\, untold chapter of A
 merican history. Called &ldquo\;thrilling&rdquo\; by <em>The Washington Po
 st</em> and &ldquo\;genius in motion&rdquo\; by the <em>San Francisco Chro
 nicle</em>\, this is theatre you feel in your body and your bones.<br /><b
 r />Don&rsquo\;t miss the return of one of the most acclaimed musicals of 
 the season.</p>
LOCATION:Daryl Roth Theatre\, 101 East 15 Street\, New York NY 10003
